    "Ensuring ethical and legal use of these tools is crucial to navigate these challenges effectively.",
    "Challenges specific to orthopedicsWhile many of the challenges, such as bias, inconsistencies and inaccuracies, are common across various fields, the reliance on precise anatomical and spatial understanding of the musculoskeletal system in orthopedics makes the risk of AI-generated inaccuracies particularly high.",
    "For instance, providing accurate representations of orthopedic imaging requires AI models trained specifically on musculoskeletal data, limiting their ability to provide accurate, specialized information.",
    "Orthopedics relies greatly on the interpretation of imaging, such as X-rays, MRIs, and CT scans.",
    "Current generative AI models struggle to reliably and consistently interpret these images, which can lead to inaccuracies in diagnosis and clinical case simulations."
